### ============================================
### INBOUND CALL TEST PAYLOADS
### Use with VS Code REST Client or curl
### Base URL: http://localhost:8081
### ============================================

### ────────────────────────────────────────────
### 1. INBOUND SIP TRUNK CRUD
### ────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1a. Create an inbound trunk (Plivo)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/inbound
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "plivo-inbound-trunk",
  "numbers": ["+911234567890"],
  "auth_username": "MANTA2NJKXNKNKXX",
  "auth_password": "MjEwYjYxNTg0OTM2ZDdjNTMyYjVhY2E5YWIyY2Rj",
  "metadata": {
    "provider": "plivo",
    "description": "Plivo trunk for India inbound calls"
  }
}

### 1b. Create an inbound trunk (Twilio)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/inbound
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "twilio-inbound-trunk",
  "numbers": ["+1234567890"],
  "auth_username": "twilio_account_sid",
  "auth_password": "twilio_auth_token",
  "metadata": {
    "provider": "twilio"
  }
}

### 1c. Create inbound trunk with multiple numbers
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/inbound
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "multi-number-inbound-trunk",
  "numbers": ["+911234567890", "+919876543210"],
  "auth_username": "sip_username",
  "auth_password": "sip_password",
  "metadata": {
    "provider": "plivo"
  }
}

### 1d. List all inbound trunks
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/inbound

### 1e. Delete an inbound trunk (replace ST_xxxxx)
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/inbound/ST_xxxxx


### ────────────────────────────────────────────
### 2. SIP DISPATCH RULE CRUD
### ────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2a. Create dispatch rule (minimal)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/dispatch-rules
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "inbound-agent-rule",
  "trunk_id": "ST_xxxxx",
  "room_prefix": "inbound_",
  "prompt": "You are a healthcare assistant at MantraCare. A patient is calling you. Greet them warmly and help them with their health-related queries. Ask how you can assist them today.",
  "voice": "arushi",
  "model": "openai"
}

### 2b. Create dispatch rule (Hindi-focused)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/dispatch-rules
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "hindi-inbound-rule",
  "trunk_id": "ST_xxxxx",
  "room_prefix": "inbound_hindi_",
  "prompt": "Aap MantraCare se baat kar rahe hain. Aapka swagat hai. Kripya bataayein ki aap kya sahayata chahte hain.",
  "voice": "arushi",
  "model": "openai"
}

### 2c. Create dispatch rule (custom model/voice)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/dispatch-rules
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "gemini-inbound-rule",
  "trunk_id": "ST_xxxxx",
  "room_prefix": "inbound_gemini_",
  "prompt": "You are a medical receptionist. Greet the caller and help them book an appointment or connect with the right department.",
  "voice": "vikas",
  "model": "gemini"
}

### 2d. List all dispatch rules
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/dispatch-rules

### 2e. Delete a dispatch rule (replace SR_xxxxx)
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/dispatch-rules/SR_xxxxx


### ────────────────────────────────────────────
### 3. OUTBOUND CALL TEST (existing system)
### ────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3a. Trigger outbound call via webhook
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/webhooks/telephony
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "event_name": "telephony_dispatch",
  "call_id": "test_1717000000",
  "client_name": "Rahul Sharma",
  "client_phone": "9876543210",
  "client_country_code": "91",
  "trunk_id": "ST_xxxxx",
  "call_from": "+911234567890",
  "prompt": "You are calling from MantraCare to follow up on the patient's recent health checkup. Ask if they are feeling better and if they need to schedule a follow-up appointment.",
  "voice": "arushi",
  "model": "openai",
  "lead_id": "lead_123",
  "stage_id": 5,
  "stageDetails": [
    {"stage_id": 1, "description": "Not answering / Failed call"},
    {"stage_id": 2, "description": "Not interested"},
    {"stage_id": 3, "description": "Follow up / Call later"},
    {"stage_id": 4, "description": "Shown interest"},
    {"stage_id": 5, "description": "Confirmed the appointment"}
  ],
  "client_custom_fields": {
    "city": "Mumbai",
    "age": 35
  },
  "call_custom_fields": {
    "campaign": "summer_checkup_2026"
  }
}

### 3b. Outbound call with DeepSeek model
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/webhooks/telephony
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "event_name": "telephony_dispatch",
  "call_id": "test_1717000001",
  "client_name": "Priya Singh",
  "client_phone": "8765432109",
  "client_country_code": "91",
  "trunk_id": "ST_xxxxx",
  "call_from": "+911234567890",
  "prompt": "You are calling from MantraCare to remind the patient about their upcoming appointment tomorrow at 10 AM.",
  "ai_payload": {
    "ai_model": "deepseek",
    "voice_id": "vikas",
    "voice_speed": 1.1
  }
}

### 3c. Manual dispatch test (no phone call, just agent in room)
POST http://localhost:8081/dispatch-test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "call_id": "test_manual_001",
  "client_name": "Test User",
  "prompt": "This is a test conversation. Ask the user about their health and well-being.",
  "voice": "arushi",
  "model": "openai"
}


### ────────────────────────────────────────────
### 4. PLIVO UNIFIED ENDPOINT (outbound)
### ────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4a. Provision Plivo trunk + place call
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/outbound/plivo
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "trunk": {
    "name": "plivo-outbound-trunk",
    "address": "phone.plivo.com",
    "numbers": ["+911234567890"],
    "auth_user": "MANTA2NJKXNKNKXX",
    "auth_pass": "MjEwYjYxNTg0OTM2ZDdjNTMyYjVhY2E5YWIyY2Rj"
  },
  "client_phone": "9876543210",
  "client_country_code": "91",
  "call_id": "plivo_test_001",
  "prompt": "You are calling from MantraCare for a health checkup follow-up.",
  "call_from": "+911234567890"
}

### 4b. Provision trunk only (no call)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/outbound/plivo
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "trunk": {
    "name": "plivo-trunk-only",
    "address": "phone.plivo.com",
    "numbers": ["+911234567890"],
    "auth_user": "MANTA2NJKXNKNKXX",
    "auth_pass": "MjEwYjYxNTg0OTM2ZDdjNTMyYjVhY2E5YWIyY2Rj"
  }
}


### ────────────────────────────────────────────
### 5. OUTBOUND TRUNK CRUD
### ────────────────────────────────────────────

### 5a. Create Zadarma outbound trunk
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/outbound/zadarma
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "zadarma-test-trunk",
  "address": "sip.zadarma.com",
  "numbers": ["+911234567890"],
  "authUsername": "zadarma_username",
  "authPassword": "zadarma_password"
}

### 5b. Create Twilio outbound trunk
POST http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/outbound/twilio
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "twilio-test-trunk",
  "address": "live-kit-mc.pstn.twilio.com",
  "numbers": ["+1234567890"],
  "auth_user": "twilio_sid",
  "auth_pass": "twilio_auth_token"
}

### 5c. List all outbound trunks
GET http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/outbound

### 5d. Delete outbound trunk
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/v1/sip/trunks/outbound/ST_xxxxx


### ────────────────────────────────────────────
### 6. UTILITY
### ────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6a. Health check
GET http://localhost:8081/health

### 6b. Get LiveKit config (for frontend)
GET http://localhost:8081/config

### 6c. Serve frontend UI
GET http://localhost:8081/
